trailingComments.value: * * Returns an Observable that emits the same values as the source observable with the exception of a `complete`. * A `complete` will cause the emission of the Throwable that cause the complete to the Observable returned from * notificationHandler. If that Observable calls onComplete or `complete` then retry will call `complete` or `error` * on the child subscription. Otherwise, this Observable will resubscribe to the source observable, on a particular * Scheduler. * * * * @param {notificationHandler} receives an Observable of notifications with which a user can `complete` or `error`, * aborting the retry. * @param {scheduler} the Scheduler on which to subscribe to the source Observable. * @return {Observable} the source Observable modified with retry logic. * @method repeatWhen * @owner Observable
